title: DiskjockeyED
author: DiskjockeyED
content: Hello guys!Happy new year Today? I repair a 0 asic hashboard. To begining, it was just a RI signal problem appear on chip 30, I just replace him.Now, RI signal is good in every row (1,8v).all CLK signal and everyone are on 0,9 (lowest is 0,896v). So I guess all its okay.all each core between next row are 0,4v (lowest is 0,394v). So its okay too ?But when I run the miner, he detect 0 ASIC. In miner status I got my pool, fan, and one line after antminer shows "ASIC 0 ; IDEAL HS 0; REAL TIME HS 0;" So I guess my hashboard is detected normaly ? I check my datacable, and PSU cable, all is good cuz with another hashboard everything is great.I post my kernel log here if anyone see something...ThanksCode:[    0.000000] Booting Linux on physical CPU 0x0[    0.000000] Linux version comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: If its far from recommended value or its abnormal then there is a possibility of shorted parts.I would suggest you read the guide from zeusbtc here https://www.zeusbtc.com/manuals/Antminer-S9-Hash-Board-Repair-Guide.aspRead under Equal voltage under that link.And I would like to ask if how many hashboard are connected to this miner it seems only one hashboard is detected according to logs?

comments.author: DiskjockeyED
comments.body: What do you found far from good value ? CLK isn't 0.9 normal value ? and RI 1.8 ?Yes I've only one hash on this conjtrol boad (its my test board)

comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: Quote from: DiskjockeyED on January 11, 2023, 06:42:12 PMWhat do you found far from good value ?
